# 43-spark — Delivery Plan

> **Project**: EVA-JP v1.2 Frontend Rebuild via GitHub Spark  
> **Version**: 1.1 — February 24, 2026 10:33 PM ET  
> **Owner**: AICOE EVA Team  
> **Horizon**: 4 weeks to production-ready Codespace baseline

---

## Objective

Produce a clean React 18 / `@eva/ui` / `@eva/gc-design-system` / WCAG 2.1 AA / bilingual EN-FR frontend for EVA-JP v1.2 using GitHub Spark as the scaffolding accelerator, then graduate to a GitHub repository under the `31-eva-faces` monorepo for team collaboration and Copilot coding agent augmentation.

---

## Guiding Principles

1. **Prompt-first, code-second** — exhaust Spark natural-language iteration before touching raw code.
2. **One acceptance criterion per iteration** — each Spark prompt targets a specific feature or quality gate.
3. **Never break what works** — each iteration validates against the full AC list before proceeding.
4. **Codespace is the editorial layer** — Spark scaffolds structure; Copilot agent mode in the Codespace refines details, handles edge cases, and wires real API calls.
5. **Accessibility is non-negotiable** — no AC-02 (axe-core) failures ever ship.

---

## Phase Structure

```
Phase 0 — Prompt Engineering      (complete — this folder)
Phase 1 — Spark Bootstrap          (Spark: initial prompt)
Phase 2 — Shared Components        (Spark: iteration 2)
Phase 3 — Screens                  (Spark: iterations 3–4)
Phase 4 — Quality Pass             (Spark: iteration 5 + Codespace agent)
Phase 5 — Repository & CI          (GitHub repo + Actions)
Phase 6 — Codespace Hardening      (Copilot coding agent)
```

---

