## Phase 4 — Quality Pass

Goal: close every remaining AC gap; enforce constraints that Spark may have drifted from.

**Spark Prompt**: Block 5 from `prompts/FINAL-SPARK-PROMPT.md`  
**Cost**: 4 premium Copilot requests

Checklist (iterate until all pass):
- `grep -r "@fluentui/react\"" src/` → 0 results (no v8 imports)
- `grep -r "style={{" src/` → 0 hardcoded hex values
- Every `makeStyles` with colour → `@media (forced-colors: active)` block present
- `grep -rn "from '@fluentui/react-components'" src/ | grep -E "Button[^G]|Input[^P]|Select[^O]|Dialog[^T]|Drawer|Badge|DataGrid|Spinner|TabList|Textarea|Toast"` → 0 results (AC-16)
- `grep -r "GCThemeProvider" src/index.tsx` → ≥ 1 result; `<FluentProvider` in `index.tsx` → 0 results (AC-16)
- All 16 AC items in `ACCEPTANCE.md` verified manually

---

## Phase 5 — Repository & CI

Goal: connect Spark to a GitHub repository; set up CI to block regressions.

Steps:
1. In Spark UI → **"Create repository"** → two-way sync enabled
2. Clone locally: `git clone <repo>`
3. Add GitHub Actions workflow:
   - `npm run build` on every PR
   - `axe-core` Playwright test suite (one test per screen)
   - TypeScript strict check: `tsc --noEmit`
4. Branch protection: require CI green before merge

---

## Phase 6 — Codespace Hardening

Goal: use Copilot coding agent to close any remaining gaps that require codebase-level reasoning.

Assign as GitHub Issues (assign to Copilot):
- "Wire all mock API calls to real `/api/*` endpoints"
- "Add keyboard navigation tests for ChatHistory drawer"
- "Add NVDA + JAWS screen reader test notes to ACCEPTANCE.md"
- "Implement retryAsyncFn utility and apply to Math Tutor"
- "Implement eventSourceRef lifecycle in TDA screen"

---

## Risk Register

| Risk | Likelihood | Mitigation |
|------|-----------|------------|
| Spark generates raw Fluent v9 instead of `@eva/ui` wrappers | High | Constraints stated in every prompt; AC-16 + Phase 4 grep catches bypasses |
| Spark drifts to inline styles or v8 components | Medium | Constraints stated twice per prompt; quality-pass iteration catches leaks |
| French translations are machine-duplicates of English | Medium | Phase 0 locale audit; FR validation gate in AC-03 |
| axe-core failures on DataGrid keyboard nav | Medium | Use `EvaDataGrid` from `@eva/ui` — wraps Fluent v9 DataGrid with ARIA natively |
| Spark exceeds token context for large prompts | Low | Prompts are split into 5 iterations; each is < 2 000 tokens |
| `@media (forced-colors: active)` missing on new components | High | Skill file `a11y-wcag.md` forces this; quality-pass prompt checks it |

---

## Success Definition

The rebuild is complete when:
- All 16 AC items in `ACCEPTANCE.md` pass
- `vite build` exits 0 with `tsc --noEmit` clean
- `axe-core` scan shows 0 critical / 0 serious on all 8 screens
- Language toggle confirmed in both EN and FR by a francophone reviewer
- Windows High Contrast (black + white) tested manually on all screens
